Source: %%PACKAGE%%
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: %%PACKAGE_VENDOR%%
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 11),
               linux-libc-dev,
               libssl-dev,
               libpcre2-dev,
               pkg-config,
               clang,
               llvm,
               cargo,
               rustc
Standards-Version: 4.1.4
Homepage: %%HOMEPAGE%%

# freeunit is a drop-in replacement for upstream NGINX Unit: each package
# Provides/Conflicts/Replaces its "unit" counterpart so installing freeunit
# cleanly takes over from a stock "unit" install. The two are deliberately not
# co-installable. Conflicts/Replaces are unversioned on purpose -- there is no
# version of upstream "unit" we want present alongside freeunit. The literal
# "unit" here is the fixed upstream package name, unaffected by the RUNTIME knob.
Package: %%PACKAGE%%
Section: admin
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Provides: unit (= ${binary:Version}), %%RUNTIME%%-r%%UNIT_VERSION%%
Conflicts: unit
Replaces: unit
Description: NGINX Unit
 NGINX Unit is a runtime and delivery environment for modern distributed
 applications. It runs the application code in multiple languages
 (PHP, Python, Go, etc.), and tightly couples it with traffic delivery
 in and out of the application. Take this application server and proxy
 directly in the cloud / container environments and fully control your app
 dynamically via an API.

Package: %%PACKAGE%%-dbg
Section: debug
Architecture: any
Priority: optional
Depends: %%PACKAGE%% (= ${binary:Version}),
         ${misc:Depends}
Provides: unit-dbg (= ${binary:Version})
Conflicts: unit-dbg
Replaces: unit-dbg
Description: NGINX Unit (debug symbols)
 This package contains the debugging symbols for NGINX Unit.

Package: %%PACKAGE%%-dev
Section: libdevel
Priority: optional
Architecture: any
Depends: %%PACKAGE%% (= ${binary:Version}),
         ${misc:Depends}
Provides: unit-dev (= ${binary:Version})
Conflicts: unit-dev
Replaces: unit-dev
Description: NGINX Unit (development files)
 Library and include files required for NGINX Unit modules development.
